  <meta name="twitter:title" content="KPI Examples | Open Source KPI Database by Operately">
  <meta name="og:title" content="KPI Examples | Open Source KPI Database by Operately">
  <meta name="og:description" content="A clean, minimalist website to find the right KPIs for your work.">
  <meta name="twitter:image" content="<%= image_url("homepage-card.jpg") %>">
  <meta name="og:image" content="<%= image_url("homepage-card.jpg") %>">
<% end -%>

<div>
  <h1 class="font-bold text-4xl">KPI Examples: Your Ultimate Guide to Key Performance Indicators</h1>

  <p class="mt-4">Effectively measuring progress and driving toward established goals and objectives has never been more crucial. Enter <span class="font-semibold">Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)</span>: quantifiable metrics used to evaluate the success of an organization or of a particular activity in which it engages.</p>
  <p class="mt-4"><span class="italic">KPI Examples</span> is an extensive, <a href="/about" class="text-operately-blue hover:text-operately-dark-blue underline">open-source</a> database of business metrics designed to empower you, whether you're a startup entrepreneur, an established business leader, or an ambitious professional keen on optimizing performance.</p>

  <div class="mt-4 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl mt-8 font-semibold">Explore Categories of KPI Examples</h2>

    <p class="mt-4">Discover the right KPIs to measure your business goals based on your industry and interests:</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-4">
      <% @categories.each do |category| -%>
        <% illustration_path = category.kpis.any? ? asset_url("#{category.slug}.jpg") : asset_url("#{category.slug}-bw.jpg") -%>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow duration-300 ease-in-out">
          <a href="<%= category_path(category) %>" class="block">
            <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden bg-cover bg-center h-32 md:h-48 relative" style="background-image: url(<%= illustration_path %>)">
              <span class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-black bg-opacity-60 text-white text-lg font-bold rounded-md"><%= category.name.titleize %></span>
              </span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600"><%= category.summary %></p>
          </a>
        </div>
      <% end -%>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-8">No matter your sector or industry, our goal with <span class="italic">KPI Examples</span> is to provide a wealth of information to help you optimize performance and align your team's actions with overarching business objectives.</p>

    <p class="mt-4"><span class="font-semibold">Haven't found what you're looking for?</span> We add new KPIs and categories every week. Bookmark this and check back in a bitâ€”or just <a href="/about#contact" class="text-operately-blue hover:text-operately-dark-blue underline">tell us what you were looking for</a>.</p>

    <div class="text-base mt-8">
      <hr/>
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg mt-4">Best Practices for Successfully Adopting KPIs</h2>

      <p class="mt-4">Successfully adopting KPIs can propel your organization forward, ensuring a data-driven approach and alignment with your core objectives. Let's dive into some proven strategies to make the most of your KPIs:</p>

      <h3 class="underline decoration-dotted font-semibold mt-4">1. Prioritize Relevant KPIs</h3>
      <p class="mt-2">Less is more: focus on the most impactful and actionable KPIs that align closely with your business goals and objectives. KPIs are not meant to make you feel good, but to change your behavior by helping you pick a course of action.</p>

      <h3 class="underline decoration-dotted font-semibold mt-4">2. Regularly Review and Adjust</h3>
      <p class="mt-2">Stay agile by periodically reviewing your KPIs and don't hesitate to drop and/or replace metrics that are no longer relevant. As the business landscape evolves, ensure your KPIs remain relevant and reflective of your current objectives.</p>

      <h3 class="underline decoration-dotted font-semibold mt-4">3. Balance Quantitative with Qualitative Insights</h3>
      <p class="mt-2">While KPIs provide quantifiable insights, don't forget the importance of qualitative feedback. For example, complement metrics like ticket times with insights into customer satisfaction and service quality.</p>

      <h3 class="underline decoration-dotted font-semibold mt-4">4. Adopt a Holistic Approach</h3>
      <p class="mt-2">While financial KPIs are critical, also incorporate indicators that shed light on customer satisfaction, employee morale, and product quality. A well-rounded view ensures all facets of your business thrive.</p>

      <h3 class="underline decoration-dotted font-semibold mt-4">5. Set Achievable Targets</h3>
      <p class="mt-2">Set targets that are ambitious yet realistic. This strikes the right balance, motivating teams while ensuring tangible progress.</p>

      <h3 class="underline decoration-dotted font-semibold mt-4">6. Always Link KPIs to Action Steps</h3>
      <p class="mt-2">Ensure that every KPI is backed by a clear action plan. This transforms data into actionable insights, driving positive change.</p>

      <h3 class="underline decoration-dotted font-semibold mt-4">7. Educate Your Team</h3>
      <p class="mt-2">Equip your team with the knowledge of what KPIs are, their significance, and how they're used to ensure collective alignment and understanding.</p>

      <p class="mt-4">With these best practices in hand, you're poised to harness the power of KPIs, effectively gauging performance over time and steering your business towards its objectives.</p>

    </div>

  </div>
</div>
